      %h3 
        Kick start your new year with my relaxing ‘just for me’ day.
        It’s the best way to unwind, make new plans and get yourself ready for a great year ahead.
      %p
        Ending the year with a celebration always feels great and it’s good to give the past a good send off whether it's been a good year or not.
        Around this time of year I like to pause for a minute and reflect on all 12 months as I wave them goodbye and move forward with new and exciting things.
        %span.big-question
          Take a breath and relax

      %p
        I find this is also a perfect point to take some well-deserved time out and re-connect with who I am and where I am going in life.
        It’s important for me to really say goodbye to the past and work out what I want from the future.
        I like to know where I am heading next and I feel that this is the perfect time to stop and think about it all before life starts moving forward again.
        If you struggle to find the time to make new aspirations, this is a great way to ensure you take a moment to do some serious thinking.
        Establish what you really want next in life.
        I love how it helps me get ready for a new year and new beginnings and really get focus on achieving my new goals. 
