      %h3 
        How to start – think of some relaxing things to do
      
      %p
        I first started out by creating what I called ‘me time hours’ a few years ago, but I enjoyed it so much that now I now make a full day of it.
        A day actually allows me to take time out from the world and to recharge, and it also gives me much needed space to think.
        I can say that I have never missed a time out/me time day since.
        It really gives me something to look forward to after the carnage of Christmas and because of that I do it every year now.
        It’s become my favourite little secret wellbeing trick.
        If you plan your day right it will turn out to be a really great and relaxing day and could have such a positive and lasting effect for the whole year.
        Also, if you need some time out in-between Christmas and new year it’s a great relaxer,
        but feel free to fit it in wherever it suits you and just find the best time for you and your needs.
        The most important thing is to have the time to yourself, really relax and enjoy your day completely.
        If you do this you will have a greater chance of getting the most benefit from your time out day and that can lead to a genuinely positive effect on your health,
        well-being and general outlook on life itself.

