      %h3 
        Preparing for your day

      %p
        I like to start by making a list of the things I would like to eat and drink on the day to make sure I have everything I need.
        It’s a good idea to think about how you will feed yourself throughout the day.
        If you don’t want to do any major meal cooking them make sure you prepare for that in advance.
        I tend to fill the fridge with easy grab treats to last through-out the day and make sure I have a delicious and prepared meal for the evening.
        Next, I make a final list of some the relaxing things I would like to do.
        When finalizing your own list think about the lings you love to do, but don’t always have the time for.
        That way its more enjoyable and more personal to you.

      %p
        Finally I like to pick a day when the house is going to be quiet and I can be by myself.
        If you have a busy house think about when the best time would be.
        Maybe arrange to be in when everyone else to be out.
        Also, think ahead about how connected you want to be with the outside world.
        We all have responsibilities to maintain, so if you need to keep your phone close to hand then go ahead,
        but try to take some time out and don’t get lost in scrolling through what the rest of the world is up to.
        This is your time and it should be special so try to reserve it just for you.
        Think of yourself as the VIP guest in your day.

