        Making a new plan for the year ahead

      %p
        It’s around this time that you should be feeling nice and relaxed and have a clear mind to tackle the one bit of homework for the day.
        If you are not ready, then simply move it to another part of the day.
        You know what suits, so do it a bit later when you will be ready for it.
        I look forward to making a good start on this part, but only once I have had some time to relax.
        The aim is to stop for a minute and really think about the year that has just gone.
        I like to dig out my goals that I wrote for the year and remind myself what I wanted to achieve and when.
        This reflection is a great first exercise because it allows me to get in the right mindset for making setting new goals and making new plans.
        If you are new to this and it’s your first time, don’t worry.
        This can be an exciting time and you have a whole year to see what you can achieve.

